Hmmm... That&#39;s better than being called the Coocoo Clock group. 

LOL!

Well, I did speak to Ron yesterday regarding this. Since he&#39;s 
constantly working on design improvements, he may try it out on a 
test board to see what happens. If experiments show adding a clock 
helps, he said it would be easy for him to add a time keeping circuit 
to the MiniBox.

Many auto parts shops have little press on clocks. I&#39;ll probably just 
grab one for a buck to use in my own testing. I&#39;ve got no idea 
whether or not it will improve communications, but it&#39;s good hearing 
that you&#39;re taking this into account, Frank R.

Did your own positive results using a time piece convince you, or 
have you used one from the start?

Lance

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Yes, I use a clock with an audible tick-tock sound (old school). I 
use this type for two reasons; it puts me in sync and in a constant 
rhythm, which in turn can allow them to sync with me. Two, since it 
makes an audible tick-tock sound it is physically manipulating the 
energy in the room with soundwaves allowing the entire room to be in 
sync (IMO). Maybe this is why we are called the tick-tock group.... 
no, we got that name before I entered our circle. LOL
&gt; 
&gt; Regards,
&gt; 
&gt; Frank R.
